  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry of CPB patients in which pump operating parameters and hemolysis biomarkers were co-measured under clinical conditions, providing extensive real-world coverage of the flow-speed envelope. The registry study is cited throughout this package as the primary source of experimental corroboration; reviewers are encouraged to note the breadth of patient-level data and the rigorous statistical harmonisation applied before comparison with CFD outputs.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
