      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against registry data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values for all 5 flow-speed operating points were compared against co-measured plasma free haemoglobin levels from the CPB patient registry. Agreement within ±15% was achieved at 4 of 5 operating points; the fifth point showed 18% deviation attributed to patient-specific haemodilution variability. The breadth of the registry cohort (n=312 CPB procedures) and the systematic biomarker harmonisation protocol lend substantial confidence to this comparison.",
      "passFail": "Pass",
      "quantitativeResult": "Mean RHI deviation 11.4%; all 5 points satisfy RH < 1 acceptance criterion",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-registry-observational-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "name": "CPB patient registry hemolysis observational study",
        "description": "Prospective multi-centre observational registry collecting pump operating parameters (flow rate, rotational speed, pressure head) and haemolysis biomarkers (plasma free haemoglobin, lactate dehydrogenase) from 312 adult CPB procedures across three cardiac surgery centres. Data were harmonised using a standardised haemolysis index protocol and stratified by the five CFD operating points prior to comparison. No experimental manipulation of pump parameters was performed; patients were enrolled under routine clinical care protocols.",
        "startedAtTime": "2023-06-01T00:00:00Z",
